name: Houston Weather
summary: Houston is experiencing severe weather conditions with multiple articles reporting impending storms. Current weather in Houston is pleasant, but a severe weather threat looms on Thursday. Severe storms with hail and strong winds are expected between 2pm and 6pm on Monday. Over 23,000 people have lost power in Houston on Monday afternoon. A timeline for storms on Thursday, May 16 has been released, and the latest thunderstorm watch indicates that the risk of hail and wind has shifted south. The Gulf Coast has been hit by deadly severe storms with winds reaching 82 mph, baseball-sized hail, and tornadoes. Severe storms are moving through the Houston area, particularly in the Harris County area, and flooding is occurring in previously flooded areas. The heaviest storms are moving east of Houston, but showers and storms are still likely tonight.

name: Mirage Las Vegas
summary: The Mirage Hotel & Casino, a Las Vegas icon, will close its doors on July 17, 2024, after 34 years of operation. The closure marks the end of an era for the city's iconic Las Vegas Strip. The Mirage, known for its signature volcano eruption show, will be transformed into the Hard Rock Hotel Las Vegas. The closure comes as part of a larger redevelopment plan for the Las Vegas Strip, which includes the addition of new hotels, restaurants, and attractions. The Mirage's volcano show will continue to operate until the closure date, and guests with existing reservations are being notified of the change.
